# Canonical Artifact Contracts

Artifact paths come from project config. Generated instructions must not hardcode product-specific roadmap, status, phase, or handoff paths.

{{ artifacts.table }}

## Design Document Contract

- Every task-level design document starts from the configured design template.
- Downstream phases should reference stable semantic sections, not fragile section numbers.
- When architecture overrules the design document, update the design document or record the divergence before implementation continues.

## Handoff Contract

- Detailed investigation, repro steps, code snippets, and fix guidance belong in handoff files.
- Orchestrator-visible reports stay compact and point to handoff artifacts.
